{"id":14880799,"mediaExerciseId":"37172fa0-9ca6-4d3b-93a9-3a8fa8c4e288","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612275,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":85,"solutions":[{"id":5949857,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the inventory turnover, days’ sales in inventory, and how long a unit of inventory sit on the shelf before it was sold for King Corporation.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we proceed with the first requirement, let us first define inventory turnover.\n\n**Inventory turnover** measures how fast the company can replace its inventory.\n\nThe formula is denoted as follows:\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Inventory turnover}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Cost of Goods Sold}} {\\text{Average Inventory}}\\\\ \\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/55ca4b91eb3e58f6f77076e7defbaccc/18d0d67af827a803290c0587346b38f6/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/55ca4b91eb3e58f6f77076e7defbaccc/18d0d67af827a803290c0587346b38f6/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"To determine the inventory turnover:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Inventory turnover}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Cost of Goods Sold}} {\\text{Average Inventory}}\\\\ \\\\\n& = \\frac{\\$4,981,315} {\\$386,735}\\\\ \\\\\n&= \\boxed{12.88}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nIn conclusion, the inventory turnover for King Corporation is 12.88.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":274,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/55ca4b91eb3e58f6f77076e7defbaccc/39963b8ce62a8d6912ae8a89cec59199/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":139,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/55ca4b91eb3e58f6f77076e7defbaccc/39963b8ce62a8d6912ae8a89cec59199/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we proceed with the second requirement, let us first define days’ sales in inventory.\n\n**Days’ sales in inventory** shows the number of days it takes for the company to sell its inventories.\n\nThe formula is denoted as follows:\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Days’ sales in inventory}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Ending inventory}} {\\text{Cost of Goods Sold}} \\times {\\text{365 days}}\\\\ \\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/55ca4b91eb3e58f6f77076e7defbaccc/763f734d8a11e1bc3b5a04120a476782/lateximg_large.png","width":898},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/55ca4b91eb3e58f6f77076e7defbaccc/763f734d8a11e1bc3b5a04120a476782/lateximg.png","width":450}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Days’ sales in inventory}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Ending inventory}} {\\text{Cost of Goods Sold}} \\times {\\text{365 days}}\\\\ \\\\\n& = \\frac{\\$386,735} {\\$4,981,315}  \\times {\\text{365}}\\\\ \\\\\n&= \\boxed{28.47}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nIn conclusion, the days’ sales in inventory for King Corporation. is 28.47.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":269,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/55ca4b91eb3e58f6f77076e7defbaccc/4d6f05e5837d334b775bba81b6ca2c56/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":137,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/55ca4b91eb3e58f6f77076e7defbaccc/4d6f05e5837d334b775bba81b6ca2c56/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"On average, a unit of inventory sat on the shelf for 28.47 days before it was sold.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/55ca4b91eb3e58f6f77076e7defbaccc/de16e9b21f8c40898aa66bc6f4874f91/lateximg_large.png","width":963},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/55ca4b91eb3e58f6f77076e7defbaccc/de16e9b21f8c40898aa66bc6f4874f91/lateximg.png","width":482}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"70eba817-db1f-4ae9-b1dd-f1d1033ccad8","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880800,"exerciseName":"5","page":85,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"5ecfed36-68ad-4525-8c50-a660705b95cf","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-questions-and-problems-5-5ecfed36-68ad-4525-8c50-a660705b95cf"},{"id":14880801,"exerciseName":"6","page":85,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"bc027c55-c071-4e48-ae61-4c62705ae54a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundame